1
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:16,733
I'm sorry, but your jokes
are not helping.

2
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:20,833
If we can find a reason
to laugh, why deprive ourselves?

3
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:23,500
I want you to feel the same way.

4
00:00:23,567 --> 00:00:25,800
Come on! I don't know
how you can take our situation

5
00:00:25,867 --> 00:00:26,833
so lightly.

6
00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:28,833
We're so helpless
on this island.

7
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:30,700
We're in the middle of nowhere.

8
00:00:30,767 --> 00:00:32,867
You don't have the right
to judge me.

9
00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:34,567
You don't know
what I'm going through.

10
00:00:34,667 --> 00:00:36,400
What my family is going through.

11
00:00:36,467 --> 00:00:41,000
Yenyen's flight failed
to reach Manila.

12
00:00:41,067 --> 00:00:43,033
They think it crashed.

13
00:00:43,100 --> 00:00:44,467
I had a dream about my mom.

14
00:00:44,533 --> 00:00:45,533
What happened?

15
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:47,067
We got separated.

16
00:00:47,133 --> 00:00:51,400
The family that accused her
has a lot of power.

17
00:00:51,467 --> 00:00:55,300
There's still no news
about Eden's plane crash.

18
00:00:55,367 --> 00:00:57,133
Is there a chance that
they will find my daughter?

19
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,600
Amanda, God has mercy.

20
00:00:58,667 --> 00:01:00,767
It's the Ramoses' fault.

21
00:01:00,833 --> 00:01:04,267
I wouldn't be in this prison
if they didn't accuse me.

22
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:06,500
My daughter and I
wouldn't get separated.

23
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:07,533
Red!

24
00:01:18,967 --> 00:01:20,467
Yenyen.

25
00:01:20,533 --> 00:01:21,500
Is this yours?

26
00:01:22,767 --> 00:01:23,800
Good thing you found it.

27
00:01:23,867 --> 00:01:25,400
Thank you.

28
00:01:25,467 --> 00:01:26,900
You're up early.

29
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:30,867
I woke up early
to find resources.

30
00:01:30,933 --> 00:01:34,133
You seem tired,
so I didn't wake you up.

31
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,267
I'm okay now.

32
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:38,267
But you're right.
We have to do something.

33
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:43,067
Let's explore the other side
of the island.

34
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:44,933
There are more trees and plants
in that area.

35
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:47,367
I'm sure we'll find
some food there.

36
00:01:47,433 --> 00:01:50,200
Right. We may find some
survivors there too.

37
00:01:50,267 --> 00:01:51,300
- Let's go. Let's look for them.
- Come on.

38
00:01:51,367 --> 00:01:52,333
I'll lead the way. Let's go.

39
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:51,933
I don't want to lose
another child.

40
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:54,800
No.

41
00:03:03,333 --> 00:03:04,667
Rina.

42
00:03:04,733 --> 00:03:06,867
It's still too early
for you to drink.

43
00:03:11,133 --> 00:03:14,267
Don't lecture me, Victor.

44
00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:15,833
Where's our son?

45
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:19,600
What's going on? Answer me!

46
00:03:19,667 --> 00:03:21,867
Do the rescuers have a lead now?

47
00:03:21,967 --> 00:03:24,467
Where is our son?

48
00:03:24,533 --> 00:03:27,433
They can't give us
any information for now.

49
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:28,700
Of course,
they're searching the area

50
00:03:28,767 --> 00:03:30,433
where the plane
could possibly have crashed.

51
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:32,900
But it's going to take some time
given the number of islands

52
00:03:32,967 --> 00:03:34,400
they have to search.

53
00:03:34,467 --> 00:03:35,700
What's going to happen
to our son?

54
00:03:35,767 --> 00:03:37,633
Can he survive?

55
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:39,067
Our son is resourceful.

56
00:03:40,100 --> 00:03:41,633
Let's just hope for the best.

57
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:51,833
Victor, I can't just sit around.

58
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:53,967
Let's do something.

59
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:56,767
Anything, please.

60
00:03:56,833 --> 00:03:59,100
I want our son back.

61
00:03:59,167 --> 00:04:01,967
I want our son back alive,
Victor.

62
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:04,233
I want our son back alive.

63
00:04:04,300 --> 00:04:05,300
Okay.

64
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:18,367
Red, hurry up!

65
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:19,433
I'm right here.

66
00:05:06,633 --> 00:05:08,367
Try this.

67
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:09,667
Is this safe to drink?

68
00:05:09,733 --> 00:05:10,967
It's clean.

69
00:05:11,033 --> 00:05:12,100
It's rainwater.

70
00:05:12,167 --> 00:05:14,833
It's not like the acid rain
we get in the city.

71
00:05:15,967 --> 00:05:18,833
And the fiber
from the coconut shell

72
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:20,900
serves as a natural filtration.

73
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:23,033
Really?

74
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:25,733
- Yes.
- Where did you learn it?

75
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:27,033
I learned it from my coach.

76
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:28,233
Miss Vinluan.

77
00:05:29,267 --> 00:05:30,700
She's not just my coach
and mentor.

78
00:05:30,767 --> 00:05:33,233
She also stands in
as my second mom.

79
00:05:34,433 --> 00:05:37,167
You seemed very fond of her.

80
00:05:37,233 --> 00:05:39,833
She's more than a coach
and mentor to me.

81
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:43,533
I also see her as my mom.

82
00:05:44,667 --> 00:05:50,167
She's always there to encourage
me whenever I feel down.

83
00:06:12,167 --> 00:06:13,267
Why are you here?

84
00:06:14,733 --> 00:06:16,400
You're supposed to be
eating your lunch.

85
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:18,667
Coach, I just got done.

86
00:06:18,733 --> 00:06:20,233
I'm just resting for a bit.

87
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:23,867
Here, eat this.

88
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,633
Your body can't get weak.

89
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,933
We still have a lot
of training to do.

90
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,033
I'm okay.

91
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:32,367
You should eat that.

92
00:06:33,467 --> 00:06:35,400
No, Yenyen.

93
00:06:35,467 --> 00:06:38,800
I always see you hiding here
during lunch break.

94
00:06:38,867 --> 00:06:41,133
You don't eat lunch.

95
00:06:41,233 --> 00:06:43,667
You're filling your stomach
with water.

96
00:06:45,033 --> 00:06:46,133
I'm sorry, Coach.

97
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:50,900
I just have enough money
for transportation.

98
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:56,733
I understand that life is tough.

99
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:02,900
But don't be embarrassed
to ask for help,

100
00:07:02,967 --> 00:07:04,867
especially from me.

101
00:07:04,933 --> 00:07:07,967
It's my responsibility
to help you out.

102
00:07:08,033 --> 00:07:09,733
So, eat.

103
00:07:11,167 --> 00:07:13,200
Thank you, Coach.

104
00:07:13,267 --> 00:07:15,100
You're such a kind person.

105
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:18,300
It's nothing.

106
00:07:19,533 --> 00:07:21,033
As your coach,

107
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:23,600
it's my responsibility
to take care of you.

108
00:07:23,667 --> 00:07:25,500
Especially your health.

109
00:07:25,567 --> 00:07:28,267
And you're my star player.

110
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:29,467
And above all...

111
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:32,767
I'm like your mother.

112
00:07:37,533 --> 00:07:39,833
Go ahead and eat.

113
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:40,833
Finish all of it.

114
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:43,700
Thank you, Coach.

115
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,000
Yenyen!

116
00:07:57,067 --> 00:07:58,300
What are you doing?

117
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:00,600
I'm sorry, Coach.

118
00:08:01,733 --> 00:08:03,500
I'm sorry for losing.

119
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:07,800
I made a lot of mistakes.

120
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:11,700
Good.

121
00:08:11,767 --> 00:08:14,167
What? What's good about it?

122
00:08:16,067 --> 00:08:18,933
It's a good thing that
you're aware of your mistakes.

123
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:21,500
Now, learn from it.

124
00:08:22,567 --> 00:08:26,300
And make sure
that you don't mess up again

125
00:08:26,367 --> 00:08:27,667
on your next game.

126
00:08:31,267 --> 00:08:36,700
You know, that's the difference
between winners and losers.

127
00:08:36,767 --> 00:08:40,300
Losers only cry
their hearts out.

128
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:43,567
Drowning themselves
in their frustrations.

129
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,800
But winners...

130
00:08:48,033 --> 00:08:49,233
knows how to get up

131
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:52,133
and fight.

132
00:09:02,233 --> 00:09:04,033
She helped me out a lot.

133
00:09:06,433 --> 00:09:11,267
I really hope we'll find her.

134
00:09:17,467 --> 00:09:19,400
Red, look at this.

135
00:09:21,167 --> 00:09:22,167
Why is this here?

136
00:09:23,233 --> 00:09:25,467
Do you think there are
other survivors here?

137
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:28,867
I hope there are
other survivors.

138
00:09:28,967 --> 00:09:29,933
Let's keep searching.

139
00:09:34,033 --> 00:09:35,633
Yen, let's follow that sound.

140
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:36,500
Come on!

141
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:51,500
Ma'am...

142
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:58,700
Can you expedite
my release papers?

143
00:09:58,767 --> 00:10:01,867
I really need to get out now.

144
00:10:03,233 --> 00:10:07,067
What? They just released
the result of your appeal

145
00:10:07,133 --> 00:10:08,600
the other day.

146
00:10:08,667 --> 00:10:11,267
It doesn't mean you can get out
of prison right away.

147
00:10:11,333 --> 00:10:15,533
We should wait for the release
orders before I can let you go.

148
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,833
I know.

149
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:20,167
But I have a situation.

150
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:27,233
The plane that my daughter
boarded crashed.

151
00:10:29,333 --> 00:10:32,033
They still haven't found her.

152
00:10:33,033 --> 00:10:40,233
Maybe I can get out
of here sooner.

153
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:44,100
I want to find her myself.

154
00:10:46,133 --> 00:10:49,033
I'm sorry about what happened,
Amanda.

155
00:10:49,100 --> 00:10:53,767
But I don't think I can grant
your request.

156
00:10:53,833 --> 00:10:56,267
Let's just wait for your papers.

157
00:10:56,333 --> 00:10:57,800
It won't take that long.

158
00:10:57,867 --> 00:10:58,967
You will be released soon.

159
00:11:14,767 --> 00:11:16,033
What's going on here?

160
00:11:17,133 --> 00:11:18,200
Ma'am!

161
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:21,367
Angelo!

162
00:11:21,433 --> 00:11:22,467
Angelo!

163
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:25,167
What happened?

164
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:27,567
Angelo!

165
00:11:27,633 --> 00:11:29,667
What happened to my son?

166
00:11:31,533 --> 00:11:32,567
Angelo!

167
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:38,133
What happened to my son?

168
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:40,600
What happened to him?

169
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:41,867
You monster!

170
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:44,667
Angelo!

171
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:48,800
No!

172
00:11:53,467 --> 00:11:54,467
Rina?

173
00:12:03,533 --> 00:12:04,500
Victor...

174
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:13,833
I dreamed again of what
that woman did to our son.

175
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:16,767
She's a monster!

176
00:12:17,767 --> 00:12:19,700
A beast!

177
00:12:19,767 --> 00:12:21,233
She's a monster.

178
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:22,733
Stop.

179
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:23,733
That's enough.

180
00:12:24,733 --> 00:12:26,767
Victor, I can't have peace.

181
00:12:29,533 --> 00:12:31,100
Especially now
that I know that demon

182
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:32,967
is getting released from prison.

183
00:12:33,033 --> 00:12:36,800
Rina, I know it's hard
to understand,

184
00:12:36,867 --> 00:12:43,033
but we should worry more
about Red now.

185
00:12:45,067 --> 00:12:47,233
We need to find our son.

186
00:13:03,433 --> 00:13:04,433
Help!

187
00:13:09,133 --> 00:13:10,100
Help!

188
00:13:12,867 --> 00:13:13,800
Coach!

189
00:13:16,433 --> 00:13:18,000
- Yenyen.
- Yenyen, help me get this up.

190
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,400
I'll take that side.

191
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:23,567
Hang in there, Coach.

192
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:27,600
One, two, three!

193
00:13:31,033 --> 00:13:32,067
Coach!

194
00:13:32,133 --> 00:13:34,433
I'm glad you're safe!

195
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:36,100
Are you okay?

196
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,733
- How are you?
- I'm okay.

197
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:42,233
How are you?

198
00:13:42,300 --> 00:13:43,333
I'm okay now.

199
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:44,300
Let's go.

200
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:46,300
Okay.

201
00:13:46,367 --> 00:13:47,733
Can you get up?

202
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:48,800
Yes.

203
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:52,767
Yen!

204
00:13:54,133 --> 00:13:55,067
Coach.

205
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:56,533
Coach, you're wounded!

206
00:13:58,133 --> 00:13:58,800
Coach!

207
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:02,133
Coach, what should we do?

208
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,867
Don't panic.

209
00:14:05,933 --> 00:14:06,967
I'm okay.

210
00:14:08,133 --> 00:14:09,133
It's a shallow wound.

211
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:11,533
Listen up.

212
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:19,900
I just need a clean cloth.

213
00:14:19,967 --> 00:14:21,133
Clean cloth.

214
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,533
Clean cloth.

215
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,633
I also need alcohol.

216
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:26,333
To clean the wounds.

217
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:28,000
We have liquor in the luggage.

218
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,767
We also have some cloth.

219
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:31,267
Okay.

220
00:14:31,333 --> 00:14:35,800
Help me get up, and we'll go
to where your luggage is.

221
00:14:35,867 --> 00:14:36,833
Okay.

222
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:40,067
Slowly.

223
00:14:44,933 --> 00:14:45,933
Be careful.

224
00:14:50,033 --> 00:14:51,633
Coach, I'm glad you're safe.

225
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:55,367
Yenyen, I'm glad
to see you again.

226
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:59,067
What about Raichu?

227
00:14:59,133 --> 00:15:01,200
Did she survive too?

228
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,900
I haven't found her yet.

229
00:15:02,967 --> 00:15:05,500
I'm here with Red.

230
00:15:05,567 --> 00:15:06,567
He is Red.

231
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:10,500
You look familiar.

232
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:14,100
I'm also a varsity
at the university.

233
00:15:16,300 --> 00:15:18,533
Thank you for saving me.

234
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:19,667
You're welcome.

235
00:15:22,233 --> 00:15:23,767
- Coach!
- Coach!

236
00:15:23,833 --> 00:15:27,333
Coach, what can we do
to help you?

237
00:15:28,967 --> 00:15:30,800
Go get your stuff
and bring it here.

238
00:15:30,867 --> 00:15:32,833
- Go on.
- Coach, I won't leave you.

239
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:34,467
I'll stay right here.

240
00:15:34,533 --> 00:15:36,233
Yenyen, I can handle this.

241
00:15:36,333 --> 00:15:37,433
Go on.

242
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:39,567
I'll go get it.

243
00:15:39,633 --> 00:15:40,900
Okay, hurry up, son.

244
00:15:40,967 --> 00:15:43,267
We have to stop the bleeding.

245
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:44,400
Okay.

246
00:15:48,267 --> 00:15:49,200
Coach...

247
00:15:50,267 --> 00:15:52,133
I talked to Mr. Akashi.

248
00:15:53,067 --> 00:15:54,800
He agreed to our deal,

249
00:15:54,867 --> 00:15:56,933
but he has some questions
regarding the business.

250
00:15:59,033 --> 00:16:02,233
Rina, are you listening to me?

251
00:16:03,933 --> 00:16:05,000
Yes.

252
00:16:05,067 --> 00:16:07,300
I know you're worrying
about Red,

253
00:16:07,367 --> 00:16:10,867
but I need your decision
for our business.

254
00:16:15,733 --> 00:16:17,767
I'm not just worried about Red.

255
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:22,267
I'm also thinking about Amanda.

256
00:16:25,267 --> 00:16:27,000
The woman you put to jail?

257
00:16:28,267 --> 00:16:29,233
Yes.

258
00:16:30,733 --> 00:16:33,000
Did you know that they're going
to release her from prison?

259
00:16:34,267 --> 00:16:36,167
How did that happen?

260
00:16:36,233 --> 00:16:38,400
The court approved her appeal.

261
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,433
I want you to do something.

262
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:47,600
I want to take revenge
before she gets out of prison.

263
00:16:49,667 --> 00:16:51,067
What do you want me to do?

264
00:16:52,733 --> 00:16:54,733
Find a connection
inside the prison.

265
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,067
Bribe them!

266
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:02,933
I want you to hurt her
before she gets released!

267
00:17:03,933 --> 00:17:05,767
Is that all?

268
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:06,900
That's easy.

269
00:17:06,967 --> 00:17:08,100
I got this.

270
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:12,833
Give her something...

271
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,367
that she will never forget.

272
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:24,567
Coach, how are you feeling?

273
00:17:24,633 --> 00:17:26,000
I'm okay.

274
00:17:26,067 --> 00:17:27,167
Don't worry, Yenyen.

275
00:17:27,233 --> 00:17:31,867
I really thought we wouldn't see
each other again.

276
00:17:31,933 --> 00:17:33,933
But nothing is impossible.

277
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,233
Because we're here now.

278
00:17:41,533 --> 00:17:43,400
Here's all the stuff.

279
00:17:43,467 --> 00:17:44,433
Good.

280
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:49,967
What I'll ask you to do
won't be easy.

281
00:17:50,067 --> 00:17:51,933
Especially from you, Red.

282
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,733
But I know I can trust you.

283
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,667
Okay?

284
00:17:56,733 --> 00:17:57,733
All right.

285
00:18:05,433 --> 00:18:06,400
Coach!

286
00:18:06,467 --> 00:18:07,467
Coach!

287
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:24,067
Coach, I'm worried.

288
00:18:27,700 --> 00:18:28,733
I can bear it.

289
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:29,567
I can do this.

290
00:18:30,567 --> 00:18:33,200
My wound won't get better
until we get this out.

291
00:18:33,267 --> 00:18:34,800
We have to remove it.

292
00:18:36,367 --> 00:18:40,100
Remember the first aid
I taught you?

293
00:18:40,167 --> 00:18:44,267
Put pressure on my wound
once Red gets the stick out.

294
00:18:44,333 --> 00:18:46,467
And then wrap it up
with a cloth.

295
00:18:46,533 --> 00:18:47,633
Do you understand, Yenyen?

296
00:18:48,733 --> 00:18:49,933
- Okay, Coach.
 - Okay?

297
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,167
- Okay.
 - Okay.

298
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:53,200
Are you ready now, Red?

299
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:56,500
Red!

300
00:18:56,567 --> 00:18:57,867
Yes, Coach.

301
00:18:57,933 --> 00:18:59,067
Okay.

302
00:18:59,133 --> 00:19:00,833
On three.

303
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:01,767
One...

304
00:19:02,633 --> 00:19:03,600
Two...

305
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:05,833
Three!

306
00:19:13,967 --> 00:19:14,967
I'm sorry.

307
00:19:39,633 --> 00:19:40,600
Coach!

308
00:19:41,633 --> 00:19:42,600
Coach!

309
00:19:43,733 --> 00:19:45,267
Coach!

310
00:19:45,333 --> 00:19:46,300
Coach!

311
00:19:46,367 --> 00:19:47,267
Coach!

312
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:48,800
- Coach, wake up!
- Coach!

313
00:19:48,867 --> 00:19:49,700
- Coach!
 - Coach!

314
00:19:49,767 --> 00:19:51,167
- Coach!
 - Coach!

315
00:19:54,500 --> 00:19:55,567
Coach!

316
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:02,467
Coach!

317
00:20:02,567 --> 00:20:03,533
Coach!

318
00:20:07,367 --> 00:20:09,200
Very good!

319
00:20:09,267 --> 00:20:10,300
Very good!

320
00:20:11,267 --> 00:20:12,300
You did great!

321
00:20:13,467 --> 00:20:16,533
Coach, have some water.

322
00:20:27,033 --> 00:20:28,667
Biscuit.

323
00:20:28,733 --> 00:20:30,433
Eat something.

324
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:32,633
- We have a biscuit here.
- Save it for later.

325
00:20:32,700 --> 00:20:34,900
I'm not hungry.

326
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,000
Coach.

327
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,933
Coach, you have to get better,
okay?

328
00:20:42,367 --> 00:20:44,467
Of course. What are you
thinking?

329
00:20:44,533 --> 00:20:46,933
I won't die here.

330
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:52,567
Never. All three of us will
get out of this island alive.

331
00:20:52,633 --> 00:20:56,567
And hopefully,
we'll find more survivors.

332
00:21:05,267 --> 00:21:06,200
One more thing.

333
00:21:07,267 --> 00:21:08,567
I have something to give you.

334
00:21:13,833 --> 00:21:14,867
Coach.

335
00:21:16,033 --> 00:21:19,133
I got this
before the plane crashed.

336
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:22,667
And I thought to myself,

337
00:21:24,833 --> 00:21:29,033
I would give this to you
in person.

338
00:21:34,267 --> 00:21:35,400
Thank you.

339
00:21:37,800 --> 00:21:41,833
You should never lose hope.

340
00:21:42,867 --> 00:21:44,700
Use it as your strength.

341
00:21:45,933 --> 00:21:48,533
You will get through
all your trials.

342
00:21:49,967 --> 00:21:51,467
Just be brave.

343
00:21:52,667 --> 00:21:53,833
Remember that, Yenyen.

344
00:21:54,800 --> 00:21:55,833
Yes, Coach.

345
00:21:56,867 --> 00:21:59,400
The mind is more powerful
than any struggles.

346
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:08,300
Now, what else do you have
in your luggage?

347
00:22:09,300 --> 00:22:12,067
There must have something
we can use.

348
00:22:13,867 --> 00:22:15,600
We have balloons.

349
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:18,167
Tarpaulin...

350
00:22:18,233 --> 00:22:19,200
Tarp.

351
00:22:20,267 --> 00:22:22,900
We can use that
to make a shelter.

352
00:22:23,933 --> 00:22:25,600
Go get it.

353
00:22:25,667 --> 00:22:31,267
We also need some branches
and sticks to build our shelter.

354
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:32,267
Okay.

355
00:22:32,333 --> 00:22:33,433
- Go on. I'll be fine.
- Are you sure?

356
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:34,433
I'm okay. You can leave me here.

357
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:35,500
Can you handle it?

358
00:22:36,833 --> 00:22:38,167
Move. Go on.

359
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:52,233
Is that her?

360
00:22:52,300 --> 00:22:53,333
Yes, that's her.

361
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:54,333
Very good.

362
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:55,800
Who are you talking to?

363
00:22:55,867 --> 00:22:57,000
Was that your brother?

364
00:22:57,067 --> 00:22:58,733
- It's coming!
- The rain is coming!

365
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:00,400
Yes! Just in time!

366
00:23:01,867 --> 00:23:03,567
Hurry up! I'm thirsty!

367
00:23:03,633 --> 00:23:04,700
Me, too!

368
00:23:04,767 --> 00:23:05,800
Do you need something?

369
00:23:05,867 --> 00:23:08,333
I just want to sharpen this
on your throat!

370
00:23:13,900 --> 00:23:15,900
Don't try to fight me!

371
00:23:15,967 --> 00:23:18,100
I just want to give you
a souvenir!
